President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the inauguration of Bernardo Arévalo in Guatemala City, Guatemala on January 14, 2024. The delegation will be led by Samantha Power, Administrator of the United States Agency for International Development. Other members of the delegation include Patrick Ventrell, Chargé d’Affaires at the United States Embassy in Guatemala City, Norma J. Torres and Lou Correa, United States Representatives from California, Philip H. Gordon, Assistant to the President and National Security Advisor to the Vice President, Katie Tobin, Deputy Assistant to the President and Coordinator for the Los Angeles Declaration, Brian A. Nichols, Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs, and Tobin Bradley, Ambassador-Designate of the United States to the Republic of Guatemala.